Description: Build mcp 1.27.1 against Noble's archive without uv-dynamic-versioning
 Four groups of changes bundled into one patch because they share the
 goal of letting Noble's python3-hatchling 1.21 produce a wheel from
 the upstream sdist:
 .
 * Replace the dynamic `[tool.hatch.version]` source
   `uv-dynamic-versioning` (which is not in Noble and requires `uv`)
   with a static `version = "1.27.1"`. The same string was already
   embedded in the sdist's `PKG-INFO`, so the resulting wheel metadata
   is identical to upstream's. The orphaned `[tool.uv-dynamic-versioning]`
   and `[tool.uv]` blocks become dead weight and are removed alongside
   `[dependency-groups]` (uv-specific) and `[tool.uv.workspace]` /
   `[tool.uv.sources]` (the workspace and dev/docs groups only matter
   inside a `uv sync`).
 * Drop runtime dependencies Noble's archive does not carry. The
   `pydantic-settings` and `sse-starlette` runtime pins are only
   reached from FastMCP's HTTP / SSE transports and from
   `mcp.server.sse` / `mcp.server.streamable_http`. Avalan's `server`
   extras exercise only the JSON-RPC types and the stdio transport,
   neither of which touches those modules. Callers that opt into the
   HTTP transports get a clear ImportError pointing them at the
   missing package. The `pyjwt[crypto]` `[crypto]` extra is dropped
   for the same reason — the OAuth handlers live behind a Bearer-auth
   middleware that Avalan does not mount; the resulting jwt symbols
   are only reachable through `mcp.server.auth.*`. The Windows-only
   `pywin32` pin is dropped because it is unreachable on Linux and
   Noble has no python3-pywin32.
 * Soften runtime-dependency floors that fall above Noble's archive
   versions for modules whose eagerly-loaded code paths use only
   stable API surface. `httpx >= 0.27.1` -> `>= 0.26` (Noble ships
   0.26.0; mcp uses `AsyncClient`, `Timeout`, `Auth`, and `codes` —
   all stable since 0.25). `jsonschema >= 4.20.0` -> `>= 4.10`
   (Noble ships 4.10.3; mcp uses `validate` and `ValidationError` —
   present since 4.0). `uvicorn >= 0.31.1` -> `>= 0.27` (Noble ships
   0.27.1; uvicorn is only loaded through FastMCP's `run_sse_async()`
   path, which Avalan does not invoke). `pyjwt >= 2.10.1` -> `>= 2.7`
   (Noble ships 2.7.0). `typing-inspection >= 0.4.1` -> `>= 0.4.2`
   to mirror the Avalan PPA's existing pin. `pydantic >= 2.11.0` ->
   `>= 2.6` so the Avalan PPA's hand-packaged pydantic 2.6.4 (capped
   by Noble's rustc 1.75 / maturin 1.3.2 toolchain at pydantic-core
   2.16.3) satisfies the constraint; mcp's eagerly-loaded modules
   reach only `BaseModel`, `ConfigDict`, `Field`, `RootModel`,
   `AnyUrl`, `UrlConstraints`, `FileUrl`, `TypeAdapter`,
   `validate_call`, and `ValidationError`, all stable since pydantic
   2.0.
 * Drop the `[project.scripts]` console-script entry that installs
   `/usr/bin/mcp`. The CLI imports `typer` (which is not in our
   Depends) and exits with a clear error message if it is missing,
   so the binary as installed by the .deb would be broken on first
   invocation. Removing the entry avoids shipping a non-functional
   script and silences lintian's `no-manual-page` warning. Users who
   want the CLI can `pip install mcp[cli]` into a venv.
Author: Avalan Packaging Team <avalan@avalan.ai>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-19

